 Cooking For Beginners

 A brief overview of techniques and simple recipes that anyone can follow.

 What you need:
  A clean work space. When cooking, it is important to keep your cooking station clean and tidy.
  Something to clean with. You don't want to be using dirty plates, bowls, or jars.
  Ingredients. Even lower quality ingredients can be turned into a good meal, whether bought from the store or gathered yourself you need something to get started.
  Recipes. While some simpler snacks can be made without much prep, it is better to follow written instructions for anything more complicated than toast.

  A few easy recipes anyone can make with a little practice

  Sausage Sandwich
 Ingredients: 1 loaf of bread, 1 sausage
 Steps:
  1. Cut the bread and the sausage into slices
  2. Put the sausage on the bread for an easy snack!

  Cvarzi
 Ingredients: Salo of the boar
 Steps:
  1. Cube the salo into small pieces, about 2cm each
  2. Fry over high heat until crisp

  Toast and Jam
 Ingredients: Loaf of bread, jam (my favorite is berry)
 Steps:
  1. Cut the bread into slices
  2. Apply a thick layer of jam

  Jerky
 Ingredients: Any meat, spice mix
 Steps:
  1. Make sure your meat is clean, and then apply the spice mix evenly
  2. Leave to dry, preferably for a day or more

